        <div class="two-third individual-content">
            <h2>Meet Thomas</h2>
            <h4>Born June 2001</h4>
            <p>Thomas would really like to be adopted. He mentions this a lot to his caseworker, who describes Thomas as polite, respectful and “a very pleasant kid to be around.”</p>
<p>“I really enjoy the time I spend interacting with him,” his worker said. “He is very insightful about his feelings and emotions.”</p>
<p>Thomas also would really like to live in a place where he can play school sports – football, soccer and basketball, particularly basketball.</p>
<p>“He wants to be accepted by peers his own age,” said his cas<img class="  wp-image-401 alignright" src="https://www.hckids.org/wp-content/uploads/Thomas-Nieman-0601sbtn-150x150.jpg" alt="Thomas Nieman 0601sbtn" width="346" height="346" srcset="https://www.hckids.org/wp-content/uploads/Thomas-Nieman-0601sbtn-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.hckids.org/wp-content/uploads/Thomas-Nieman-0601sbtn-300x300.jpg 300w, https://www.hckids.org/wp-content/uploads/Thomas-Nieman-0601sbtn.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 346px) 100vw, 346px" />e manager. “He’s introverted, but he has a really good sense of humor.”</p>
<p>In his current placement, he has become a role model, she said, “and everyone looks up to him.”</p>
<p>He wants a family that will appreciate his needs,” the case manager said. “He needs freedom, he needs some space. He’s a good kid.”</p>
<p>Thomas likes to read and is good at it. He earns all As in school. He also loves to ride his skateboard and scooter.</p>
<p>He’s earning allowance for his good behavior. He’s saving the money for an MP3 player.</p>
<p>Thomas would like a home with pets.</p>

